name: Sup-R-Drop
short_description:
• Ideal for flush-mounting applications

  • Preassembled for ease of installation

  • Female threads accept standard UNC bolts or threaded rods (1/4" to 3/4")
  • Slotted body is precision-matched to tapered internal plug for uniform expansion
  • Knurled body increases friction connection between anchor and wall of hole

name: Taper Bolt
short_description:
• Required hole diameter equals anchor diameter

  • Variation in hole size can be accommodated by turning the expander nut

  • Equipment may be removed and replaced. The bolt is simply re-inserted and torqued to obtain original holding power (the nut stays in the hole)
  • Bolt can be removed and re-used with a new nut after cleaning and lubricating the threads
  • Strength – the highest shear strength of any expansion anchor

  • Withstands vibratory loads

  • Works in a bottomless hole
size_info: Anchor Dia. & Length: 3/8” x 2-1/4”, Hole Dia.: 3/8", Min. Embed.: 1-7/8", Required Torque to set (ft. lbs.): 40, Head Size: 9/16”, Required Head Clearance: 3/16", Tension (lbs.): 4,030, Shear (lbs.): 7,177, Tension (lbs.): 4,987, Shear (lbs.): 8,567, Box

name: Sup-R-Toggle
short_description:
• Light to medium loads under dead or variable conditions in a variety of

  • hollow base materials
